29 public officials or the employer, and such employee's right of free petition,
30 lawful assemblage and free speech.
31 (2) To prohibit or prevent any election of the officers of any labor
32 organization.
33 (3) On and after July 1, 1955, To participate in any strike, walk-out,
34 or cessation of work or continuation thereof against an employer when any
35 of such employer's employees are organized into a collective bargaining
36 unit without the same being authorized by a majority vote of the

